definitions.definition: Any of the eukaryotic , usually unicellular organisms —including protozoans , slime molds and some algae —historically grouped into the kingdom Protista (or Protoctista ), now distributed over several clades ; any eukaryote that is not a plant , animal or fungus .

subdefinitions.definition: Any single-celled eukaryote , prokaryote or sponge [to 1959] .

main_definition: ( microbiology ) Any of the eukaryotic , usually unicellular organisms —including protozoans , slime molds and some algae —historically grouped into the kingdom Protista (or Protoctista ), now distributed over several clades ; any eukaryote that is not a plant , animal or fungus .
